# Track the durable TEXT store (documents/commits/refs/manifest.json = source of
# truth) so the KB survives clone/reclaim. Ignore ONLY the rebuildable index cache
# (`git-kb reindex` regenerates it) and ephemeral working state. Same rule as
# `.handoff` (track text; never commit binary rebuild caches). See META-ORG-POLICY
# P5.23 (.kb/store durability). NOTE: `git-kb init` ignores `store/` wholesale by
# default — that makes the KB non-durable and MUST be overridden in every member.
.backup/
.cache/
backups/
cache/
store/stashes/
workspaces/
worktrees/
